      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "DetermineFirstPeriodCanceledByAccountElseFromDate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. It is designed to determine the first period a specific account was canceled. If no cancellation is found, it defaults to returning a specified date. This function is typically used in scenarios where understanding the cancellation timeline of accounts is crucial, such as in subscription-based services or financial applications."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this function is considered medium. This is due to its reliance on querying potentially large datasets to determine the cancellation period, as well as handling conditional logic to return either a cancellation date or a default date."
        }
      ]
    },
